*riakc-2.1.1_p20151111 (07 Jun 2016)

  07 Jun 2016; Amadeusz Żołnowski <aidecoe@gentoo.org> +metadata.xml,
  +riakc-2.1.1_p20151111.ebuild:
  Add new package

  It is debundled from net-im/ejabberd-16.04 and therefore inherits
  keywords from ejabberd: ~amd64, ~arm, ~ppc and ~x86. ~ia64 and ~sparc
  are not inherited because other dependency is missing these keywords and
  there's no chance it can get them any time soon.

  Package-Manager: portage-2.3.0_rc1

  03 Jul 2016; Amadeusz Żołnowski <aidecoe@gentoo.org>
  riakc-2.1.1_p20151111.ebuild:
  dev-erlang: Add ~ia64 and ~sparc keywords back

  These packages have been debundled from ejabberd which used to have
  ~ia64 ~sparc keywords. These had to be removed temporarily until
  dev-util/rebar has these keywords.

  09 Jul 2016; Amadeusz Żołnowski <aidecoe@gentoo.org>
  riakc-2.1.1_p20151111.ebuild:
  Restrict Erlang version to <19

  It doesn't build with >=dev-lang/erlang-19.0.

  Package-Manager: portage-2.3.0

  20 Aug 2016; Matthias Maier <tamiko@gentoo.org>
  riakc-2.1.1_p20151111.ebuild:
  stabilize 2.1.1_p20151111 on amd64/x86, bug #587908

  Package-Manager: portage-2.2.28

  20 Aug 2016; Anthony G. Basile <blueness@gentoo.org>
  riakc-2.1.1_p20151111.ebuild:
  stabilize 2.1.1_p20151111 on ppc, bug #587908

  Package-Manager: portage-2.2.28

  29 Aug 2016; Amadeusz Żołnowski <aidecoe@gentoo.org>
  riakc-2.1.1_p20151111.ebuild:
  Die on rm failure

*riakc-2.4.1 (29 Aug 2016)

  29 Aug 2016; Amadeusz Żołnowski <aidecoe@gentoo.org> +riakc-2.4.1.ebuild:
